I just bought a 1974 Chevrolet 3/4 ton 4x4 pickup truck. I'm having a bit of
trouble with it. Whenever I put the 4WD shifter in neutral, the truck won't
move in any of the gears on the column. But if I put it in 4WD it drives just
fine. Is this a transfer box problem or a tranny problem?

BTW- when the 4WD shifter is in neutral and I put the column shifter in park,
there is a terrible sound of gears screeching to a halt. The truck also won't
go into park when the 4WD shifter is in neutral.

Any help or suggestions will be greatly appreciated, thanks.

--Tony

</POST>



<POST>
<POSTER> Richard Nixon </POSTER>
<POSTDATE> 1999-02-27T12:00:00 </POSTDATE>
Email: Richard Nixon &lt;richard.ni ... @worldnet.att.net&gt;
